Class IntArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.PrimitiveCollection
      • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.array.PrimitiveArray
        • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.array.scalars.IntArray
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.esotericsoftware.kryo.KryoSerializable, IntCollection, IntIterable, IntList, PrimitiveList, Initializable, NamedObject, Countable, Sized, CompressibleCollection
    public final class IntArray
extends PrimitiveArray
implements IntList
    A dynamic array of primitive int values. Supports the indexing operations in IntList. Expands the size of the array if you call set(int, int) or add(int) and the array is not big enough.

    Constructors take the same name, maximum size and estimated capacity that all PrimitiveCollections take. In addition a IntArray can construct from part or all of a primitive int[].

    A sub-array can be retrieved by specifying the starting index and the length with subArray(int, int). The sub-array is read only and will share data with the underlying parent array for efficiency.

    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
    See Also:
    PrimitiveCollection, IntList, KryoSerializable, CompressibleCollection, CompressibleCollection
